---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Fertility Preservation" description="Guide to fertility preservation including egg freezing, sperm freezing, and embryo freezing. Learn about costs, success rates, and storage considerations.">
	<section class="hero-mini">
		<div class="container">
			<nav class="breadcrumb">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<a href="/treatments/">Treatments</a>
				<span>‚Üí</span>
				<span>Fertility Preservation</span>
			</nav>
			<h1>Fertility Preservation</h1>
			<p>Freezing eggs, sperm, or embryos to protect future fertility options.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="intro-box">
				<h2>Overview</h2>
				<p>Fertility preservation allows you to freeze reproductive cells for future use. This can be for medical reasons (before cancer treatment) or elective reasons (delaying parenthood). Modern vitrification techniques have dramatically improved survival rates for frozen eggs and embryos.</p>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Egg Freezing (Oocyte Cryopreservation)</h2>

			<div class="preservation-card main">
				<div class="card-icon">ü•ö</div>

				<div class="who-should">
					<h3>Who Should Consider Egg Freezing</h3>
					<div class="reasons-grid">
						<div class="reason-item medical">
							<span class="label">Medical</span>
							<span class="text">Before chemotherapy, radiation, or gonadotoxic treatments</span>
						</div>
						<div class="reason-item elective">
							<span class="label">Elective</span>
							<span class="text">Delaying parenthood for career, education, or personal reasons</span>
						</div>
						<div class="reason-item medical">
							<span class="label">Transition</span>
							<span class="text">Before hormone therapy for gender transition</span>
						</div>
						<div class="reason-item medical">
							<span class="label">Family History</span>
							<span class="text">Of early menopause</span>
						</div>
						<div class="reason-item medical">
							<span class="label">Endometriosis</span>
							<span class="text">Which can damage ovarian reserve over time</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="callout-box warning">
					<div class="callout-icon">‚è∞</div>
					<div class="callout-content">
						<h4>Age Matters Significantly</h4>
						<p>Egg quality declines with age. For best outcomes, freeze before age 35-36. Freezing after 38 results in lower success rates per egg.</p>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="age-table">
					<h3>Egg Freezing by Age</h3>
					<div class="table-container">
						<table>
							<thead>
								<tr>
									<th>Age at Freezing</th>
									<th>Eggs Retrieved</th>
									<th>Eggs Needed for ~1 Baby</th>
									<th>Success Rate</th>
								</tr>
							</thead>
							<tbody>
								<tr class="optimal">
									<td>&lt;35</td>
									<td>10-20</td>
									<td>10-15 eggs</td>
									<td><span class="rate excellent">70-80%</span></td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>35-37</td>
									<td>8-15</td>
									<td>15-20 eggs</td>
									<td><span class="rate good">50-60%</span></td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>38-40</td>
									<td>5-10</td>
									<td>20-30 eggs</td>
									<td><span class="rate moderate">30-40%</span></td>
								</tr>
								<tr>
									<td>&gt;40</td>
									<td>3-8</td>
									<td>30+ eggs</td>
									<td><span class="rate low">15-25%</span></td>
								</tr>
							</tbody>
						</table>
					</div>
					<p class="table-note">Multiple cycles may be needed to bank sufficient eggs.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="process-section">
					<h3>The Process</h3>
					<div class="process-steps">
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">1</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Initial consultation and testing</strong>
								<span>AMH, antral follicle count, general health</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">2</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Ovarian stimulation</strong>
								<span>10-14 days of hormone injections</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">3</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Monitoring</strong>
								<span>Ultrasounds and bloodwork every 2-3 days</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">4</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Trigger shot</strong>
								<span>36 hours before retrieval</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">5</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Egg retrieval</strong>
								<span>Outpatient procedure under sedation</span>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="step">
							<div class="step-num">6</div>
							<div class="step-content">
								<strong>Vitrification</strong>
								<span>Eggs flash-frozen and stored in liquid nitrogen</span>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h3>Costs</h3>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Egg freezing cycle</span>
							<span class="price">$6,000-$12,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Medications</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$6,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Anesthesia</span>
							<span class="price">$500-$1,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Annual storage</span>
							<span class="price">$500-$1,000/year</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item total">
							<span class="name">Total per cycle</span>
							<span class="price">$10,000-$18,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="future-use">
					<h3>Future Use</h3>
					<p>When ready to use frozen eggs:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Eggs are thawed (<span class="highlight">85-95% survival rate</span>)</li>
						<li>Fertilized with sperm via ICSI</li>
						<li>Embryos cultured and transferred</li>
						<li>Additional cost: $4,000-$8,000 for thaw + transfer cycle</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Sperm Freezing (Sperm Cryopreservation)</h2>

			<div class="preservation-card simple">
				<div class="card-icon">üî¨</div>

				<div class="card-header-content">
					<div class="callout-box success inline">
						<div class="callout-icon">‚úì</div>
						<div class="callout-content">
							<h4>Good News</h4>
							<p>Sperm freezing is simpler and less expensive than egg freezing. Sperm survive freezing well with 50-75% post-thaw survival. One sample can produce multiple vials for multiple attempts.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="who-should">
					<h3>Who Should Consider Sperm Freezing</h3>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Before cancer treatment</div>
						<div class="use-item">Before vasectomy (backup)</div>
						<div class="use-item">Military deployment</div>
						<div class="use-item">Work travel</div>
						<div class="use-item">Gender transition</div>
						<div class="use-item">Declining sperm quality</div>
						<div class="use-item">Before high-risk activities</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="process-section compact">
					<h3>The Process</h3>
					<ol class="simple-steps">
						<li>Provide sample at clinic or sperm bank</li>
						<li>Sample analyzed for count, motility, morphology</li>
						<li>Sample divided into vials and frozen</li>
						<li>Stored in liquid nitrogen indefinitely</li>
					</ol>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h3>Costs</h3>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Initial freezing and analysis</span>
							<span class="price">$300-$1,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Annual storage</span>
							<span class="price">$200-$500/year</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Embryo Freezing</h2>

			<div class="preservation-card">
				<div class="card-icon">üß¨</div>

				<div class="who-should">
					<h3>Why Freeze Embryos</h3>
					<div class="uses-grid">
						<div class="use-item">Extra embryos from IVF cycle</div>
						<div class="use-item">Before medical treatment</div>
						<div class="use-item">Both partners' gametes available</div>
						<div class="use-item">Waiting for PGT results</div>
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="success-highlight">
					<h3>Success Rates</h3>
					<p>Embryo freezing has the <strong>highest success rates</strong> of all fertility preservation methods:</p>
					<div class="success-stats">
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="value">95-99%</span>
							<span class="label">Embryo survival after thaw</span>
						</div>
						<div class="stat">
							<span class="value">Same</span>
							<span class="label">Success rates as fresh embryos</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="note">Success rates based on age at time of embryo creation</p>
				</div>

				<div class="costs-section">
					<h3>Costs</h3>
					<div class="cost-grid">
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">IVF cycle (to create embryos)</span>
							<span class="price">$12,000-$17,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Medications</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$6,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Embryo freezing</span>
							<span class="price">$1,000-$2,000</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Annual storage</span>
							<span class="price">$500-$1,000/year</span>
						</div>
						<div class="cost-item">
							<span class="name">Future FET cycle</span>
							<span class="price">$3,000-$5,000</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Ovarian Tissue Freezing</h2>

			<div class="preservation-card experimental">
				<div class="experimental-badge">Experimental Option</div>
				<div class="card-icon">üî¨</div>

				<p>Ovarian tissue is surgically removed, frozen, and later re-implanted. This option is:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Used primarily for prepubescent girls before cancer treatment</li>
					<li>An option when there's no time for egg freezing</li>
					<li>Still considered experimental at some centers</li>
					<li>Has resulted in live births when tissue is reimplanted</li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Insurance Coverage</h2>

			<div class="insurance-info">
				<div class="insurance-item covered">
					<div class="icon">‚úì</div>
					<div class="content">
						<h4>Medical fertility preservation</h4>
						<p>Many states require coverage before cancer treatment</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="insurance-item not-covered">
					<div class="icon">‚úó</div>
					<div class="content">
						<h4>Elective freezing</h4>
						<p>Rarely covered; some employers offer this benefit</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="insurance-note">Check your specific plan details</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">How Long Can Cells Be Stored?</h2>

			<div class="storage-info">
				<div class="storage-fact">
					<span class="icon">‚ùÑÔ∏è</span>
					<p>Eggs, sperm, and embryos can be stored <strong>indefinitely</strong> in liquid nitrogen</p>
				</div>
				<div class="storage-fact">
					<span class="icon">üë∂</span>
					<p>Babies have been born from embryos frozen <strong>20+ years</strong></p>
				</div>
				<div class="storage-fact">
					<span class="icon">üìä</span>
					<p><strong>No evidence</strong> of declining quality over time in storage</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<h2 class="section-title">Considerations</h2>

			<div class="callout-box warning important">
				<div class="callout-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</div>
				<div class="callout-content">
					<h4>Important</h4>
					<p>Freezing eggs or embryos does not guarantee a future baby. It's best thought of as insurance - improving your chances, but not a certainty.</p>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div class="questions-section">
				<h3>Questions to Consider</h3>
				<div class="questions-grid">
					<div class="question-item">
						<span class="q-icon">?</span>
						<span>How many eggs/embryos should I bank?</span>
					</div>
					<div class="question-item">
						<span class="q-icon">?</span>
						<span>What happens if I don't use them?</span>
					</div>
					<div class="question-item">
						<span class="q-icon">?</span>
						<span>What's my clinic's thaw survival rate?</span>
					</div>
					<div class="question-item">
						<span class="q-icon">?</span>
						<span>What are the storage costs long-term?</span>
					</div>
					<div class="question-item">
						<span class="q-icon">?</span>
						<span>If freezing embryos: What happens in case of divorce or death?</span>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>

			<nav class="nav-footer">
				<a href="/treatments/third-party/" class="nav-prev">
					<span class="nav-label">Previous</span>
					<span class="nav-title">‚Üê Third-Party Reproduction</span>
				</a>
				<a href="/treatments/surgical/" class="nav-next">
					<span class="nav-label">Next</span>
					<span class="nav-title">Surgical Treatments ‚Üí</span>
				</a>
			</nav>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>

